---
import Layout from "@/layouts/main.astro"
---

<Layout
  title="About — Where Builders Meet"
  description="Why this showcase exists and who built it."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-10">
    <div>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mb-1">🏯 About</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Why this exists.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">The game</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-foreground"><a href="https://www.wherewindsmeetgame.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Where Winds Meet</a></strong> is an open-world action RPG set in ancient China.
        Among its many features is a guild base system — a shared space that guilds can
        design, build, and decorate together. The results range from cozy mountain villages to
        sprawling imperial palaces.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Why this site</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        It all started after touring tons of incredible guild bases in Where Winds Meet — they were simply too good to keep secret! ✨
        So this place was born: somewhere to share cool builds, swap ideas, and get inspired together.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        The problem? There's no in-game gallery, and great screenshots tend to vanish in Discord threads. This site collects all
        guild base submissions from the community Discord, ranks them by community votes, and presents them in a
        browsable showcase — no build left behind.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Hop into the Discord to show off your own base or just hang out with fellow builders! 🏗️🎮
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">How it's built</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        A bot watches the Discord forum, picks up new submissions, and counts community reactions.
        Everything syncs automatically <strong class="text-foreground">~4 times a day</strong> so the showcase stays fresh without any manual work.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="rounded-xl bg-muted/40 ring-1 ring-border px-6 py-5 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-4">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <p class="font-medium text-sm">Want to get involved?</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">Join the community Discord or check the contribute page.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-2 shrink-0">
        <a
          href="https://discord.gg/Qygt9u26Bn"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90 transition-colors"
        >
          Discord ↗
        </a>
        <a
          href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "")}/contribute`}
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full border border-border px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-muted transition-colors"
        >
          Contribute
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
